# Java Conventions

## Dependency Injection

Use constructor injection, not `@Inject` on fields. Mark dependencies `final`.

```java
// Good
@ApplicationScoped
public class MyService {
    private final SomeDependency dependency;

    public MyService(final SomeDependency dependency) {
        this.dependency = dependency;
    }
}

// Bad
@ApplicationScoped
public class MyService {
    @Inject
    SomeDependency dependency;
}
```

## Prefer `final`

- Method parameters: `final String text`
- Local variables: `final var result = ...`
- Fields: `private final SomeDependency dependency`

## Records for DTOs

Use Java records for data transfer objects. Place them in the `dto/` sub-package
of the relevant command package.

## CDI Beans

- Services are `@ApplicationScoped`
- Commands are picocli `@Command` classes implementing `Runnable`

## Logging

Use `org.jboss.logging.Logger` with `LOG.infof(...)` format-string style.

```java
private static final Logger LOG = Logger.getLogger(MyService.class);
```

## Text Blocks

Use text blocks (`"""`) for multi-line strings. Use `.formatted(...)` for interpolation.
